Class NumberTypeRepository

java.lang.Object
  org.ektorp.support.CouchDbRepositorySupport<NumberType.Default>
      ch.ethz.inf.vs.persistingservice.database.NumberTypeRepository
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.ektorp.support.GenericRepository<NumberType.Default>
public class NumberTypeRepository
extends org.ektorp.support.CouchDbRepositorySupport<NumberType.Default>

The Class NumberTypeRepository contains the methods to connect to the couchdb database and store and retrieve data from it.

It contains the standard methods of a CouchDbRepository (i.e. add, contains, remove and update) and defines more methods to retrieve data from the database.

NumberTypeRepository

public NumberTypeRepository(java.lang.Class<NumberType.Default> type,
                            org.ektorp.CouchDbConnector db,
                            java.lang.String deviceName)
Instantiates a new number type repository inheriting the standard methods add, contains, remove and update.

Parameters:
type - the type defines the default type for the standard methods.
db - the db is used to connect to the couchdb database and perform the queries.
deviceName - the device name is stored to retrieve the documents containing data for the specified device.
